NAME: Alexander Hamilton U.S. Custom House
DESCRIP: Circa-1907 National Historic Landmark housing the Museum of the American Indian & a federal court.

NAME: Alice Austen House Museum
DESCRIP: The Alice Austen House, also known as Clear Comfort, is located at 2 Hylan Boulevard in the Rosebank section of Staten Island, New York City, New York.

NAME: American Academy of Arts and Letters
DESCRIP: The American Academy of Arts and Letters is an honor society of the country's 250 leading architects, artists, composers, and writers.

NAME: American Folk Art Museum
DESCRIP: The American Folk Art Museum is the premier institution devoted to the aesthetic appreciation of folk art and creative expressions of contemporary self-taught artists from the United States and abroad.

NAME: American Museum of Natural History
DESCRIP: The American Museum of Natural History, located on the Upper West Side of Manhattan, New York City, is one of the largest museums in the world.

NAME: American Numismatic Society
DESCRIP: Museum & research center devoted to coins from all periods & cultures offering rotating exhibits.

NAME: Anne Frank Center USA
DESCRIP: The Anne Frank Center for Mutual Respect is a nonprofit organization with a focus on civil and human rights activism in the United States. The group's stated objective is to advocate "for the kinder and fairer world of which Anne Frank dreamed."

NAME: Asia Society
DESCRIP: Asian cultural center offering events, talks, performances & an art museum with diverse exhibitions.

NAME: Bartow-Pell Mansion
DESCRIP: A National Historic Landmark, it has one of the nation's finest Greek Revival interiors, and is the last surviving major mid-19th century country estate house in the Pelham Bay area.

NAME: Bowne House
DESCRIP: The Bowne House is the best-preserved example of Anglo-Dutch vernacular residential architecture in the country, and it continues to occupy its original site.

NAME: Bronx Museum of the Arts (BXMA)
DESCRIP: Specializing in contemporary art by New Yorkers of Latin, Asian & African-American descent.

NAME: Brooklyn Children's Museum
DESCRIP: Founded in 1899, it is the first museum in the United States, and according to some, the first one worldwide that caters specifically to children.

NAME: Brooklyn Museum
DESCRIP: American art is heavily represented, starting at the Colonial period. The museum also has a "Memorial Sculpture Garden" that features salvaged architectural elements.

NAME: Children's Museum of Manhattan
DESCRIP: we're a destination for delight, discovery, and learning! We create experiences at the intersection of the arts, sciences, and humanities to ensure children thrive at home, at school, and in the community.

NAME: Children's Museum of the Arts
DESCRIP: As part of its mission to promote art for all children, CMA features programs and partnerships designed for children with learning disabilities, children in foster care, and children in homeless families.

NAME: Cloisters
DESCRIP: The Cloisters is a museum in Fort Tryon Park in Upper Manhattan, New York City specializing in European medieval architecture, sculpture and decorative arts, with a focus on the Romanesque and Gothic periods.

NAME: Coney Island Museum
DESCRIP: Coney Island USA exists to defend the honor of American popular culture through innovative exhibitions and performances. Presenting and producing exciting new works, our approach is rooted in mass culture and the traditions of P.T. Barnum, dime museums, burlesque, circus sideshows, vaudeville, and Coney Island itself.

NAME: Cooper-Hewitt, National Design Museum
DESCRIP: Cooper Hewitt, Smithsonian Design Museum is a design museum located in the Upper East Side's Museum Mile in Manhattan, New York City. It is the only museum in the United States devoted to historical and contemporary design.

NAME: Dahesh Museum
DESCRIP: The Dahesh Museum of Art is the only museum in the United States devoted to the collection and exhibition of European academic art of the 19th and 20th century.

NAME: Drawing Center
DESCRIP: The Drawing Center is a Manhattan, New York, museum and a nonprofit exhibition space that focuses on the exhibition of drawings, both historical and contemporary.

NAME: Dyckman Farmhouse
DESCRIP: The Dyckman House, now the Dyckman Farmhouse Museum, is the oldest remaining farmhouse on Manhattan island, a reminder of New York City's rural past.
